It contributes to other people.
对他人有帮助

543
00:26:18,130 --> 00:26:20,500
This is research done by Barbara Fredrickson,
Barbara Fredrickson做了这项研究

544
00:26:20,500 --> 00:26:23,880
one of the faculty members who teaches at U PENN.
在宾州大学任教的学会成员

545
00:26:23,880 --> 00:26:26,430
You saw a picture of her up there.
你们曾在上面见过她的照片

546
00:26:27,180 --> 00:26:29,010
What Barbara Fredrickson says is that
Barbara Fredrickson的观点是

547
00:26:29,010 --> 00:26:34,200
positive emotions have an evolutionary reason,
积极情绪有一个进化理由

548
00:26:34,660 --> 00:26:37,930
that they have a purpose beyond just making us feel good.
它们的目的不仅仅是让人感觉好

549
00:26:37,930 --> 00:26:41,370
For example, they help us think beyond
比如它们有助我们超越

550
00:26:41,370 --> 00:26:43,930
what we are thinking right now, broaden our thinking;
现在的思考范畴 拓展我们的思想

551
00:26:43,930 --> 00:26:46,500
they help us build relationships;
有助我们建立人际关系

552
00:26:46,500 --> 00:26:48,160
they help us build capacities--
帮助我们建立能力

553
00:26:48,160 --> 00:26:50,160
remember one of the key concepts of this course
这门课的一个主要概念

554
00:26:50,160 --> 00:26:52,180
is the positive emotions,
就是积极情绪

555
00:26:52,180 --> 00:26:54,460
positive psychology as a field as a whole,
积极心理学

556
00:26:54,460 --> 00:26:57,400
is about building capacities.
就是要建立能力

557
00:26:58,010 --> 00:26:59,140
The two analogies we use
我们使用的两个类比

558
00:26:59,140 --> 00:27:05,460
was strengthening our immune system or stronger "psychological engine"
是加强我们的免役系统或加强"心理引擎"

559
00:27:05,460 --> 00:27:07,700
that has the capacity to endure more
获得更强大的忍受能力

560
00:27:07,700 --> 00:27:09,590
not just from the negative to zero,
不只是从负到零

561
00:27:09,590 --> 00:27:12,570
but also from the zero to the positive.
还要从零到正

562
00:27:13,520 --> 00:27:14,990
So this is Barbara Fredrickson.
这是Barbara Fredrickson的观点

563
00:27:14,990 --> 00:27:17,660
Let me quote extensively from her article,
我想进一步引用她的文章

564
00:27:17,660 --> 00:27:19,840
which I believe you are reading for this week,
也是你们这周要阅读的

565
00:27:20,450 --> 00:27:22,570
"We should work to cultivate positive emotions
"我们应该努力培育积极情绪

566
00:27:22,570 --> 00:27:24,570
in ourselves and in those around us,
在自己身上和周围人身上

567
00:27:24,570 --> 00:27:27,870
not just as end states in themselves,
不能只将它们作为终极状态

568
00:27:27,870 --> 00:27:31,500
but also as a means to achieving psychological growth
还要将其作为手段实现心理成长

569
00:27:31,500 --> 00:27:35,330
and improved psychological and physical health over time.
改善心理和身体的健康

570
00:27:35,330 --> 00:27:38,620
I call this the broaden-and-build theory of positive emotions
我称其为积极情绪的扩建理论

571
00:27:38,620 --> 00:27:43,400
because positive emotions appear to broaden people's momentary thought
因为积极情绪似乎能扩展人们的瞬间想法

572
00:27:43,400 --> 00:27:48,410
action repertoire and build the enduring personal resources.
和动作指令库并建立持久的个人资源

573
00:27:49,060 --> 00:27:51,600
Through experiences of positive emotions,
通过体验积极情绪

574
00:27:51,600 --> 00:27:55,140
people transform themselves,
人们实现改变

575
00:27:55,140 --> 00:27:57,770
becoming more creative, knowledgeable,
变得更有创造力 更博学

576
00:27:57,770 --> 00:28:00,850
resilient, socially integrated,
适应性更强 更易融入社会

577
00:28:00,850 --> 00:28:02,720
and healthy individuals."
获得更健康的人格"

578
00:28:02,720 --> 00:28:05,870
Numerous benefits to just experiencing positive emotions.
体验积极情绪有诸多好处

579
00:28:05,870 --> 00:28:06,580
It's a win-win.
是双赢的

580
00:28:06,580 --> 00:28:07,590
It feels good.
它让人感觉好

581
00:28:07,590 --> 00:28:11,130
And it's good for us and it's good for society as a whole
对我们有好处 对整个社会也有好处

582
00:28:11,130 --> 00:28:13,470
as I'll argue momentarily.
一会我就会解释

583
00:28:13,470 --> 00:28:15,260
So what she's talking about here, for example,
她谈到的问题包括

584
00:28:15,260 --> 00:28:18,840
is that positive emotions help us overcome negative emotions.
积极情绪有助我们克服消极情绪

585
00:28:19,260 --> 00:28:21,540
What happens when we experience negative emotions
体验消极情绪时

586
00:28:21,540 --> 00:28:22,900
is that our consciousness,
我们的意识

587
00:28:22,900 --> 00:28:26,320
our thinking narrows and constricts.
我们的思维变得狭窄 收紧

588
00:28:27,010 --> 00:28:29,160
We focus just on one thing, so for example.
只专注于一件事 比如

589
00:28:29,160 --> 00:28:30,610
And that can be a good thing--
那可能是件好事

590
00:28:30,610 --> 00:28:32,630
you know, a lion comes to and charges me,
一头狮子朝我冲过来

591
00:28:32,630 --> 00:28:35,600
"I don't want to start thinking about my MAPP application.
我不想考虑宾州大学硕士申请的事

592
00:28:35,600 --> 00:28:37,790
I don't want to start thinking about what my roommates say.
不想考虑室友说了什么

593
00:28:37,790 --> 00:28:40,490
I want to focus on the lion.
我只想考虑这头狮子

594
00:28:41,080 --> 00:28:44,470
So my consciousness narrows and constricts,
我的意识变得狭窄 收紧

595
00:28:44,470 --> 00:28:47,280
and I'm in the "fight or flight" mode.
进入"对抗或逃跑"模式

596
00:28:48,020 --> 00:28:50,780
Now that's a good thing when a lion charges me.
有狮子朝我冲来时是件好事

597
00:28:50,780 --> 00:28:53,020
But it's not a very good thing
但它变得不是很好

598
00:28:53,020 --> 00:28:56,480
if my consciousness continues to narrow
如果我的意识继续狭窄

599
00:28:56,480 --> 00:29:02,250
and constrict beyond the threat, or beyond the hardship.
收紧超出威胁 超出困难

600
00:29:03,240 --> 00:29:08,310
And what we know is that very often we enter a downward spiral,
我们知道经常会进入下行螺旋

601
00:29:08,310 --> 00:29:13,360
a vicious cycle when we go into this narrow and constrict mode.
一个恶性循环 当我们进入狭窄收紧的模式

602
00:29:13,360 --> 00:29:17,160
So for example, just for example-- a random example:
随便举个例子

603
00:29:17,160 --> 00:29:19,350
My girlfriend leaves me, alright?
女朋友离开了我

604
00:29:19,350 --> 00:29:24,240
And I narrow and constrict in terms of my thinking--
我的思维收窄缩紧

605
00:29:24,240 --> 00:29:26,770
all I am thinking about is just that.
一心只想着被女友甩了

606
00:29:27,260 --> 00:29:29,320
And what will happen is as a result,
结果就是

607
00:29:29,320 --> 00:29:32,090
I experience sadness,
我感觉悲伤

608
00:29:32,090 --> 00:29:34,680
because that is what I am thinking about, and sadness--
因为我一心只想那个 悲伤

609
00:29:34,680 --> 00:29:37,170
a painful emotion, not a positive emotion--
是一种痛苦的情绪 一种消极情绪

610
00:29:38,190 --> 00:29:41,180
leads to further narrow and constrict.
导致进一步的收窄缩紧

611
00:29:41,180 --> 00:29:42,810
And that can potentially,
那有可能

612
00:29:42,810 --> 00:29:46,100
not always, but potentially can go on and on and on.
并非总是 但可能一直持续下去

613
00:29:48,000 --> 00:29:50,350
And that's when it can become depression.
直到变成抑郁

614
00:29:51,050 --> 00:29:54,640
That's when I have difficulty getting out of this downward,
那时我将很难脱离这种下行

615
00:29:54,640 --> 00:29:56,600
vicious cycle.
恶性的循环

616
00:29:57,440 --> 00:30:00,020
Positive emotions do the opposite.
积极情绪正相反

617
00:30:00,020 --> 00:30:01,850
They broaden and build.
它们扩展建立

618
00:30:03,290 --> 00:30:07,560
Broaden and build leads to positive emotions.
扩建导致积极情绪

619
00:30:08,480 --> 00:30:11,660
Then positive emotions further broaden and build.
积极情绪再进一步扩建

620
00:30:11,660 --> 00:30:13,290
So that's a virtuous cycle.
所以是个良性循环

621
00:30:13,290 --> 00:30:14,050
And I look broadly,
我眼界宽了

622
00:30:14,050 --> 00:30:15,180
I look to othe people,
关注其他人

623
00:30:15,180 --> 00:30:17,180
I look to other things: So what can I do now?
关注其他事 思考现在我能做什么?

624
00:30:17,180 --> 00:30:19,980
Where can I go? Where can I spend my time?
我能去哪里?我把时间用在哪里?

625
00:30:20,360 --> 00:30:22,690
And very often what that does--
很经常的是

626
00:30:22,690 --> 00:30:27,360
a positive emotion can take us out of this downward spiral
积极情绪把我们带出下行螺旋

627
00:30:29,060 --> 00:30:32,260
and create an upward spiral.
形成一个上行螺旋

628
00:30:32,260 --> 00:30:35,980
A positive emotion can come in form of watching a humorous film;
积极情绪可以是看一部滑稽电影

629
00:30:36,480 --> 00:30:39,360
it can come in form of "if you take a deep breath"--
可以是"一次深呼吸"

630
00:30:39,360 --> 00:30:42,970
we talked about deep breathing when we talked about my body;
探讨"心理 身体"时会谈到深呼吸

631
00:30:43,990 --> 00:30:48,150
a positive emotion can come in form of interaction with a friend,
积极情绪可以是与朋友交流

632
00:30:48,150 --> 00:30:49,500
a pleasant one.
一次愉快的交流

633
00:30:50,120 --> 00:30:51,720
It's the positive emotion
积极情绪

634
00:30:51,720 --> 00:30:58,650
that can take us out from this downward spiral to this upward spiral.
能把我们带离这个下行螺旋进入这个上行螺旋

635
00:30:59,710 --> 00:31:03,230
And again it doesn't always take a very long time.
而且不用很久

636
00:31:04,090 --> 00:31:06,710
And the challenge is to combine "the permission to be human"
困难在于将之与准许为人相结合

637
00:31:06,710 --> 00:31:11,150
to experience the emotion to go through the motion
去体会情绪 实现转移

638
00:31:11,320 --> 00:31:15,880
and yet not to enter the downward spiral where six months later,
但不会进入下行螺旋

639
00:31:15,880 --> 00:31:18,950
after small incident, I'm still in that rot.
在发生小小意外六个月后 仍心情低落

640
00:31:20,810 --> 00:31:22,370
We'll talk about what is the right time
我们会谈到什么是合适的时候

641
00:31:22,370 --> 00:31:23,510
and how do you find the right time,
如何找到合适的时候

642
00:31:23,510 --> 00:31:24,650
how do you find the balance
以及如何在

643
00:31:24,650 --> 00:31:27,070
between thinking about painful emotions
思考痛苦情绪

644
00:31:27,070 --> 00:31:29,540
and when does it slide to rumination,
和让痛苦情绪滑入沉思到平衡

645
00:31:29,540 --> 00:31:31,040
which is not always helpful.
沉思并非总有帮助

646
00:31:33,930 --> 00:31:36,000
So it helps overcome the negative emotions.
它有助克服消极情绪

647
00:31:36,000 --> 00:31:39,060
Also, creativity-- we think broadly--
还有创造力 我们的眼界更宽

648
00:31:39,060 --> 00:31:41,050
we are able to make connections,
能产生更多联系

649
00:31:42,010 --> 00:31:45,620
see connections we haven't seen before, perhaps.
看到以前没有看到的联系

650
00:31:46,850 --> 00:31:51,910
There's a lot of the talk about the depressive creature.
有很多关于"抑郁创造者"的说法

651
00:31:51,910 --> 00:31:53,960
If you want to have high level of creativity,
如果你想拥有更高水平的创造力

652
00:31:53,960 --> 00:31:55,470
it's a must you have to be depressed.
必须承受抑郁

653
00:31:55,470 --> 00:31:58,160
Well, it turns out that's not the case.
其实并非如此

654
00:31:59,720 --> 00:32:02,020
Very often manic depressives are highly creative,
躁狂抑郁病人一般更有创造力

655
00:32:02,020 --> 00:32:05,090
but that's usually during their manic phases.
但一般在躁狂阶段

656
00:32:05,090 --> 00:32:08,940
In the depressed phase, our thinking is narrow;
在抑郁阶段 我们的思维收窄

657
00:32:08,940 --> 00:32:11,530
we don't think outside the box usually--
我们失去创造力

658
00:32:11,530 --> 00:32:14,050
of course there's many exceptions, but as a whole.
当然有例外 但总体而言没有

659
00:32:14,050 --> 00:32:15,160
In fact there's research--
实际上有这样一项研究

660
00:32:15,160 --> 00:32:20,380
for example, this was done with internists, doctors,
在内科医生 医生中间进行

661
00:32:20,380 --> 00:32:22,910
who are giving a very difficult,
向他们提出一个

662
00:32:22,910 --> 00:32:27,430
very difficult question connected to a liver problem
与肝脏问题有关的很困难的问题

663
00:32:27,430 --> 00:32:29,810
that an individual patient had.
那是一个病人的病症

664
00:32:30,220 --> 00:32:32,140
And they divided them randomly into three groups--
医生们被随机分成三组

665
00:32:32,140 --> 00:32:34,580
the first group was a control group--
第一组是对照组

666
00:32:34,580 --> 00:32:36,160
they just had to solve the problem;
他们必须解决这个问题

667
00:32:36,160 --> 00:32:40,330
the second group was given a statement
第二组听一段有关

668
00:32:40,330 --> 00:32:43,190
about humanistic value of medicine--
医学人文观的声明

669
00:32:43,190 --> 00:32:46,100
why is it so important to be a medical doctor;
为什么作医生如此重要

670
00:32:46,100 --> 00:32:51,890
and the third group was given candy
第三组得到糖果

671
00:32:51,890 --> 00:32:55,910
and put in a funny playful good mood.
让他们获得愉快放松的好心情

672
00:32:57,120 --> 00:32:59,790
The third group that was given the candies
第三组得到糖果

673
00:32:59,790 --> 00:33:02,660
and put in a positive playful mood
并获得积极愉快的心情

674
00:33:02,660 --> 00:33:05,790
outperformed the other two groups significantly--
明显比另外两组有更好表现

675
00:33:06,250 --> 00:33:08,320
they thought about more options
他们考虑更多选择

676
00:33:08,800 --> 00:33:12,760
and they actually came up with better solutions with that problem.
得出更好的问题解决办法

677
00:33:12,760 --> 00:33:15,800
And this is one of many studies in this area.
这是这个领域中的一项研究

678
00:33:16,220 --> 00:33:18,210
Another example-- children.
再举个例子 小孩子

679
00:33:18,630 --> 00:33:21,290
One group of children was a control group;
一群小孩组成对照组

680
00:33:21,290 --> 00:33:24,420
the second group was taught to think back
有人教第二组小孩回想

681
00:33:24,420 --> 00:33:27,720
to experience that make them laugh or smile.
让他们大笑或微笑的经历

682
00:33:29,080 --> 00:33:32,290
And that group did much better
第二组

683
00:33:32,290 --> 00:33:35,100
on the learning task than the control group,
在学习任务上比对照组表现更好

684
00:33:35,100 --> 00:33:36,770
because they were put into a positive mood.
因为他们被置于积极情绪

685
00:33:36,770 --> 00:33:37,760
Again, it's a win-win.
它是双赢的

686
00:33:37,760 --> 00:33:42,960
It's defined in many ways that "no pain, no gain" paradigm,
它在很多方面定义了"没有痛苦就没有回报"

687
00:33:42,960 --> 00:33:49,090
whether it's education of doctors or in school,
不论是对医生的教育还是在学校

688
00:33:49,550 --> 00:33:52,440
as well as generally in the workplace.
在一般的工作场所也一样

689
00:33:52,930 --> 00:33:54,780
Because you see, also motivation and energy--
因为动力和精力

690
00:33:54,780 --> 00:33:56,080
you don't need research for that,
不需要研究就能明白

691
00:33:56,080 --> 00:33:57,650
you know that when you are feeling good,
你知道感觉好时

692
00:33:57,650 --> 00:34:00,180
you have more motivation, you have more energy--
动力和精力更充沛

693
00:34:01,280 --> 00:34:04,020
of course, there is a lot of research to back that up.
当然有很多研究支持这一点

694
00:34:04,020 --> 00:34:05,990
And ultimately success.
最终达到成功

695
00:34:07,210 --> 00:34:08,860
They look in the professional people
他们调查专业人士

696
00:34:08,860 --> 00:34:11,240
who are able to manage their emotions
能更好地控制自己的情绪

697
00:34:11,240 --> 00:34:15,050
better and lead to positive emotions,
获得积极情绪

698
00:34:15,050 --> 00:34:19,610
get out of this narrow and constrict to the broaden and build
脱离狭窄收紧进入扩建的人

699
00:34:19,610 --> 00:34:21,950
are in the long term more successful.
长远会取得更大成功

700
00:34:21,950 --> 00:34:24,340
Again, it's not that people who don't have painful emotions--
他们不是没有痛苦情绪

701
00:34:24,340 --> 00:34:26,030
remember? They are all dead.
没有的都是死人

702
00:34:26,350 --> 00:34:29,210
It's that people who experience painful emotions
那些人经历痛苦情绪

703
00:34:29,210 --> 00:34:32,660
but are all in the same time able to shift themselves,
但同时能够更好地

704
00:34:32,660 --> 00:34:33,980
their consciousness, their thinking,
把自己 他们的意识 思想

705
00:34:33,980 --> 00:34:37,210
their experience to the positive more readily.
他们的感受向积极方向转移

706
00:34:37,210 --> 00:34:38,790
And happier people are more successful,
越快乐的人越成功

707
00:34:38,790 --> 00:34:42,220
because they have more energy and work harder.
因为他们有更多精力 工作更努力

708
00:34:42,220 --> 00:34:46,390
It's because their pursuing something
因为他们在追求

709
00:34:46,390 --> 00:34:48,490
rather than running away from something--
而不是在逃离

710
00:34:48,490 --> 00:34:52,370
it is called "approach rather than avoidance goals"--
这叫"靠近而非逃避目标"

711
00:34:52,370 --> 00:34:55,220
we'll talk about that during the week on goals.
我们将在探讨"目标"时谈到

712
00:34:55,220 --> 00:34:57,950
Also because they form better relationships.
还因为他们建立更好的人际关系

713
00:34:57,950 --> 00:35:00,240
They are more open and generous.
他们更开放更宽容

714
00:35:02,770 --> 00:35:03,940
And they are more creative.
他们的创造力更强

715
00:35:03,940 --> 00:35:07,720
All these components ultimately lead to higher levels of success.
所有这些因素最终导致更高层次的成功

716
00:35:08,460 --> 00:35:12,680
Positive emotions not only contribute to our success,
积极情绪不仅有助成功

717
00:35:12,680 --> 00:35:14,350
they don't just contribute to our feeling good,
不仅能让我们感觉好

718
00:35:14,350 --> 00:35:17,140
they also contribute to our wellbeing.
还有助我们获得幸福

719
00:35:17,140 --> 00:35:18,520
Optimistic people, and again,
乐观的人

720
00:35:18,520 --> 00:35:20,420
not Pollyannaish detached optimism,
不是指盲目的乐天派

721
00:35:20,420 --> 00:35:23,050
but grounded optimists,
而是脚踏实地的乐观主义者

722
00:35:23,360 --> 00:35:25,500
on average, live significantly longer.
平均而言 明显更加长寿

723
00:35:26,840 --> 00:35:27,780
Bless you.
保佑你们

724
00:35:27,780 --> 00:35:30,370
The immune system is stronger,
免疫系统更强

725
00:35:33,350 --> 00:35:36,270
so it also helps in terms of physical health.
所以对身体健康也有帮助

726
00:35:37,110 --> 00:35:41,740
But now the question is the moral question:
现在的问题是 道德问题

727
00:35:41,740 --> 00:35:44,390
What about other people?
那么其他人呢?

728
00:35:45,550 --> 00:35:50,950
How can I talk about or act in my life,
我谈论经营自己的生活

729
00:35:50,950 --> 00:35:55,880
pursuing my happiness isn't that selfish?
追求自己的快乐 这怎么不是自私?

730
00:35:57,550 --> 00:36:00,110
Ant the answer is: "Yes, it is selfish."
答案是"是的 那是自私"

731
00:36:00,110 --> 00:36:03,220
When I talk to myself, when I say to myself,
当我对自己说

732
00:36:03,220 --> 00:36:04,880
"I want to be happier",
"我想更快乐"

733
00:36:04,880 --> 00:36:07,640
I say to myself, "I want to be happier."
我对自己说"我想更快乐"

734
00:36:07,640 --> 00:36:09,270
That' s a selfish thing.
那是一件自私的事

735
00:36:09,880 --> 00:36:11,360
So it that bad? Is that immoral?
它是坏的吗?是不道德的吗?

736
00:36:11,360 --> 00:36:12,510
Well, in our culture,
在我们的文化中

737
00:36:12,510 --> 00:36:16,640
selfishness and immorality have essentially become synonymous.
自私和不道德成了同义词

738
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:19,200
And that's a problem.
那是个问题

739
00:36:19,200 --> 00:36:22,170
And here's why. Because this is the No. 1--
这就是为什么 因为这是头号

740
00:36:23,960 --> 00:36:29,940
equating to selfishness and immorality is the No. 1 cause--
将自私等同于不道德是头号原因

741
00:36:29,940 --> 00:36:32,930
subconsciously mostly, but not only--
多数是在潜意识里

742
00:36:32,930 --> 00:36:36,100
No. 1 cause of unhappiness.
导致不快乐的头号原因

743
00:36:36,100 --> 00:36:40,070
Because people feel guilty about pursuing their own happiness.
人们为追求自己的快乐感到内疚

744
00:36:40,070 --> 00:36:46,500
People feel guilty at times feeling good about themselves.
人们在自我感觉很好时会内疚

745
00:36:46,500 --> 00:36:49,170
How can I? How dare I feel good about myself?
我怎么可以? 我怎么敢自我感觉良好?

746
00:36:49,170 --> 00:36:51,070
How can I pursue my happiness
我怎么能追求自己的快乐

747
00:36:51,070 --> 00:36:52,890
when there is so much suffering in the world?
当世上有那么多痛苦时?

748
00:36:52,890 --> 00:36:55,180
And there is a lot of suffering in the world.
世上确有很多痛苦

749
00:36:55,800 --> 00:36:58,120
So how do we respond to that?
我们要如何回应?

750
00:37:00,930 --> 00:37:05,390
First of all, happiness is a positive sum game--
首先 快乐是正和博弈

751
00:37:05,390 --> 00:37:07,920
it's not a zero sum game.
不是零和博弈

752
00:37:08,680 --> 00:37:11,880
Neither it is a negative sum game--
也不是负和博弈

753
00:37:11,880 --> 00:37:15,410
it's not that my happiness takes away from other people's happiness
我的快乐不是从别人那里夺来

754
00:37:15,410 --> 00:37:16,910
which will be a negative sum game:
那将是负和博弈

755
00:37:16,910 --> 00:37:19,600
if I have more, you'll necessarily have less.
我有更多 你一定更少

756
00:37:21,770 --> 00:37:24,220
It's not even a zero--
甚至不是一个零…

757
00:37:25,370 --> 00:37:26,390
or rather if I have less,
或者我更少

758
00:37:26,390 --> 00:37:27,920
you'll have less- that's a negative sum game--
你也会更少 那也是负和博弈

759
00:37:27,920 --> 00:37:30,650
or a zero sum game-- if I have more, you'll have less-
或零和博弈 我更多 你就会更少

760
00:37:30,650 --> 00:37:31,960
it's a fixed pie.
饼就那么大

761
00:37:31,960 --> 00:37:32,630
It's not that.
不是这样的

762
00:37:32,630 --> 00:37:34,290
It's a positive sum game.
它是一个正和博弈

763
00:37:34,290 --> 00:37:37,040
Why? Because happiness is contagious.
为什么?因为快乐是感染的

764
00:37:37,040 --> 00:37:39,570
If I'm happier, I'm more likely
如果我更快乐 我更有可能

765
00:37:39,570 --> 00:37:43,680
to contribute to other people's happiness and wellbeing.
对他人的快乐和幸福作出贡献

766
00:37:43,680 --> 00:37:45,130
Being happy, in other words,
感受快乐 换言之

767
00:37:45,130 --> 00:37:51,870
is also a moral state in the sense of actually contributing
也是一种道德状态

768
00:37:51,870 --> 00:37:54,210
to other people's wellbeing.
对他人的幸福作出贡献

769
00:37:54,210 --> 00:37:56,810
The Buddha talked about it thousands of years ago,
佛在几千年前就谈到它

770
00:37:56,810 --> 00:38:00,040
"Thousands of candles can be lit from a single candle,
"一支蜡烛可以点燃千支蜡烛

771
00:38:00,040 --> 00:38:02,820
and the life of the candle will not be shortened.
蜡烛的生命不会被缩短

772
00:38:02,820 --> 00:38:06,240
Happiness never decreases by being shared."
分享绝不会减少快乐"

773
00:38:06,240 --> 00:38:08,550
It's like passing on light.
就像传递光明

774
00:38:09,670 --> 00:38:12,000
If you are happy, and work on your happiness,
你快乐并努力争取快乐

775
00:38:12,000 --> 00:38:15,510
you are contributing indirectly to other people's happiness,
就是间直接对他人的快乐作出贡献

776
00:38:15,510 --> 00:38:20,190
just like the baby who laughed last time-- made you laugh.
就像上次大笑的婴儿 把你们逗笑

777
00:38:21,310 --> 00:38:22,890
It's contagious.
笑是感染的

778
00:38:26,430 --> 00:38:28,370
Generally people who work on their happiness--
一般来说 努力争取快乐的人

779
00:38:28,370 --> 00:38:31,050
again, not people who experience constantly high,
再一次 不是那些总是保持快乐的人

780
00:38:31,050 --> 00:38:33,510
they would have difficulty having real relationships
那种人将很难建立人际关系

781
00:38:34,030 --> 00:38:35,250
since they are dead--
因为他们是死的

782
00:38:35,250 --> 00:38:39,590
but generally, people, those of us who are alive,
一般来说 活着的人

783
00:38:39,590 --> 00:38:40,880
who work on happiness,
努力争取快乐

784
00:38:40,880 --> 00:38:44,130
who experience the vicissitude of life-- the ups and downs--
体验生活的变迁 起起落落

785
00:38:44,800 --> 00:38:47,990
but overall work on happiness and become happier and happier,
但努力争取快乐而且越来越快乐

786
00:38:47,990 --> 00:38:50,160
have better relationships,
有更好的人际关系

787
00:38:50,190 --> 00:38:53,010
more generous, more accepting of other people,
更宽容 更接受他人

788
00:38:53,010 --> 00:38:59,470
more tolerant of other people as well as themselves.
更容忍他人和他们自己

789
00:39:01,790 --> 00:39:04,790
There's a lot of research to show that helping ourselves,
很多研究表明自我帮助

790
00:39:04,790 --> 00:39:07,340
in other words, working on our happiness,
换言之 努力为自己争取快乐

791
00:39:07,340 --> 00:39:09,510
contributing to our wellbeing,
有助我们获得幸福

792
00:39:10,360 --> 00:39:14,330
leads us to also be more generous and benevolent toward others.
也能引导我们对他人更加宽容和亲切

793
00:39:14,330 --> 00:39:16,920
This is a research by one of the leading researchers,
一位重要的研究者

794
00:39:16,920 --> 00:39:19,940
one of the first researches in the area of positive emotions,
积极情绪领域的首批研究者之一

795
00:39:19,940 --> 00:39:21,360
Alice Isen.
Alice Isen进行了这个研究

796
00:39:23,180 --> 00:39:24,520
And she showed, time and again,
她反复证明

797
00:39:24,520 --> 00:39:27,600
how feeling good is good for us and good for others,
感觉好如何对我们和他人都有益

798
00:39:30,370 --> 00:39:31,970
and it works the other way as well.
反之亦然

799
00:39:31,970 --> 00:39:34,160
This is a wonderful thing about happiness.
这是快乐很美妙的地方

800
00:39:34,160 --> 00:39:35,550
It works the other way as well,
别人快乐你也快乐

801
00:39:35,550 --> 00:39:40,480
because helping others also helps ourselves.
因为帮助他人也是帮助自己

802
00:39:40,600 --> 00:39:42,580
Remember your task for this week--
记得你们这周的任务

803
00:39:42,580 --> 00:39:44,310
a dozen of you have already read it--
一些同学已经知道

804
00:39:44,310 --> 00:39:48,520
it's to commit- above and beyond what you usually commit-
就是去做超越以往所做的事情

805
00:39:48,520 --> 00:39:53,130
five extra acts of kindness during one day.
一天内多做五件好事

806
00:39:53,510 --> 00:39:54,920
Five extra acts of kindness.
多做五件好事

807
00:39:54,920 --> 00:39:57,240
This is a research done by Sonja Lyubomirsky--
这是Sonja Lyubomirsky做过的一项研究

808
00:39:57,240 --> 00:39:58,960
I mentioned her book in the first class:
我在第一堂课提及她的书

809
00:39:58,960 --> 00:40:00,560
"The how of happiness".
《快乐之道》

810
00:40:01,550 --> 00:40:02,890
She's done fantastic work,
她很好地

811
00:40:02,890 --> 00:40:04,700
showing how people who help--
证明人们

812
00:40:04,700 --> 00:40:08,010
whether it's helping five extra acts during the week--
不论是在一周内多做五件好事

813
00:40:08,010 --> 00:40:08,980
it can be more;
可以更多

814
00:40:08,980 --> 00:40:11,200
doesn't have to be restricted to five--
不必局限于五件

815
00:40:11,550 --> 00:40:16,520
or people who help five extra acts during one day,
或者人们在一天内多做五件好事

816
00:40:17,310 --> 00:40:19,880
it's actually contributing to their wellbeing.
都能让他们更幸福

817
00:40:19,880 --> 00:40:22,240
So helping others is also helping ourselves.
帮助他人也是帮助自己

818
00:40:22,240 --> 00:40:25,840
You know, one of the things that I say and only half ingest,
我说到的一件事 只说了一半意思

819
00:40:25,840 --> 00:40:33,380
is that I know of no more selfish act and a benevolent act.
即最自私的所为就是善举

820
00:40:34,470 --> 00:40:35,620
Again, only half ingest--
只说了一半意思

821
00:40:35,620 --> 00:40:38,900
because the two are interconnected.
因为两者有内在联系

822
00:40:38,900 --> 00:40:42,250
And there is a self-enforcing loop between the two,
两者间有自我实施的循环

823
00:40:42,250 --> 00:40:45,540
where helping others helps ourselves;
帮助他人就是帮助自己

824
00:40:45,540 --> 00:40:50,120
and helping ourselves, in turn, helps others.
帮助自己继而帮助他人

825
00:40:50,120 --> 00:40:52,850
And rather than looking it as selfish--
不要把它看作自私

826
00:40:52,850 --> 00:40:54,520
some people may feel this ease way--
有人可能会这样简单考虑

827
00:40:54,520 --> 00:40:58,910
and rather than looking it as selfish i.e. -- equal immoral.
不该把自私等同于不道德

828
00:41:00,530 --> 00:41:01,550
We should look at it as something
我们应该把它视为

829
00:41:01,550 --> 00:41:04,180
that is so wonderful about our nature,
人性的美妙之处

830
00:41:04,180 --> 00:41:06,860
a part of our nature that we should celebrate.
是我们应该颂扬的本性

831
00:41:06,860 --> 00:41:09,410
The fact that our happiness is tied to others,
我们的快乐与他人的相关连

832
00:41:09,430 --> 00:41:12,660
the fact that we are tied to others in a web of empathy--
我们通过同情网络和他人相关连

833
00:41:12,660 --> 00:41:15,350
that's a wonderful thing about human nature.
那是人性的美妙之处

834
00:41:15,350 --> 00:41:19,260
A thing that we need to celebrate much more than we are doing already.
一样值得我们进一步颂扬的东西

835
00:41:19,680 --> 00:41:21,290
Because remember, if we don't celebrate,
如果不颂场

836
00:41:21,290 --> 00:41:24,540
if we don't appreciate that part of our nature,
如果我们不欣赏人性的那一部分

837
00:41:24,540 --> 00:41:28,170
that part of our nature will depreciate.
人性的那一部分将贬值

838
00:41:28,870 --> 00:41:32,300
To appreciate has two meanings as we talked about:
欣赏有两个意思

839
00:41:32,300 --> 00:41:36,650
one is to say "thank you" for something and two is to grow.
一是懂得感谢 二是传递

840
00:41:36,650 --> 00:41:38,730
If we appreciate the good in our nature,
如果我们欣赏人性中

841
00:41:38,730 --> 00:41:40,680
in our inclinations,
欲望中好的东西

842
00:41:43,330 --> 00:41:45,640
if we appreciate that part of our nature,
如果我们欣赏本性中那一部分

843
00:41:45,640 --> 00:41:48,730
it will appreciate and we'll have more of it.
它将升值 我们将获得更多

844
00:41:50,160 --> 00:41:51,850
If we look down at it and say,
如果我鄙视它并说

845
00:41:51,850 --> 00:41:52,830
"It's a terrible thing that
"很可怕

846
00:41:52,830 --> 00:41:55,430
I just derive benefits from helping other people",
我从帮助他人身上获得利益"

847
00:41:55,430 --> 00:41:58,890
then that part of our nature will depreciate over time.
那么本性中那一部分将随时间贬值

848
00:41:59,800 --> 00:42:02,450
For your readings, you are reading one of the meditations in my book,
你们正在读我书中的冥想部分

849
00:42:02,450 --> 00:42:04,590
where I talk about it a little bit more in length,
书中有更详细的阐述

850
00:42:04,590 --> 00:42:07,050
and I also gave the philosophical foundation,
也给出了哲学基础

851
00:42:07,050 --> 00:42:11,130
because in many ways this goes against "counting and thinking"
因为在很多方面有别于"数数和思考"

852
00:42:11,130 --> 00:42:16,010
that has been so dominant in our 20th and 21st century
那种方法在20和21世纪处于统治地位

853
00:42:16,010 --> 00:42:18,040
thinking about morality.
思考道德

854
00:42:19,260 --> 00:42:20,450
It feels good to feel good.
感谢好就是感觉好

855
00:42:20,450 --> 00:42:24,320
It also contributes to others to feel good.
也能让他人感觉好

856
00:42:25,050 --> 00:42:27,920
I want to end this premise idea
我想以介绍一位

857
00:42:28,840 --> 00:42:34,610
by talking a little bit about a person for whom,
一生致力于

858
00:42:35,310 --> 00:42:39,620
one of the chief purpose in life was to spread happiness--
传播快乐的人来结论这个前提

859
00:42:41,840 --> 00:42:44,670
Mahatma Gandhi. This is a story about him.
圣雄甘地 这是关于他的一个故事

860
00:42:46,740 --> 00:42:50,690
There was a woman like many people came
一个女人像很多人一样

861
00:42:51,050 --> 00:42:54,020
to ask for advice from Gandhi.
来寻求甘地的建议

862
00:42:54,020 --> 00:42:55,970
And she came from very far away.
她长途赶来

863
00:42:55,970 --> 00:42:58,320
And she brought her son along.
还带着儿子

864
00:42:59,200 --> 00:43:02,660
And she said in front-- she got audience with Mahatma,
她拜见甘地

865
00:43:02,660 --> 00:43:05,740
and she said in front of him, and she said to him
在他面前说 她对他说

866
00:43:08,000 --> 00:43:12,560
"I came from afar, because I have a problem with my son.
"我长途赶来 因为我儿子有个问题

867
00:43:12,960 --> 00:43:17,830
My son eats way too much sugar.
我儿子吃太多糖

868
00:43:19,350 --> 00:43:23,720
And I'd like you to tell him to stop it.
希望你能告诉他别吃太多糖

869
00:43:24,110 --> 00:43:26,760
Because it's hurting his health, his teeth.
因为糖损害他的健康 牙齿

870
00:43:27,660 --> 00:43:30,360
And he will listen to you. He admires you.
他会听你的 他很崇拜你"

871
00:43:31,370 --> 00:43:34,260
" Gandhi looked at her and said,
甘地看着她说

872
00:43:34,260 --> 00:43:38,140
"Madam, can you please come back in a month?"
"夫人 你能一个月后再来吗?"

873
00:43:39,880 --> 00:43:43,660
She didn't know why but she listened to him after all--
她不明白为什么但还是听了他的话

874
00:43:43,660 --> 00:43:45,170
he was Gandhi.
因为他是甘地

875
00:43:45,480 --> 00:43:47,360
She left, went far away,
她离开 长途返回

876
00:43:47,360 --> 00:43:49,880
came all the way back a month later,
一个月后又回来

877
00:43:49,880 --> 00:43:53,380
and once again, got an audience with Gandhi.
再次与甘地见面

878
00:43:53,380 --> 00:43:55,500
She said in front of him,
她在他面前说

879
00:43:55,500 --> 00:43:56,900
She said "I was here a month ago."
她说"一个月前我来过"

880
00:43:56,900 --> 00:43:58,880
And he said, "Yes. I remember."
他说"是的 我记得"

881
00:43:59,310 --> 00:44:01,280
And she said, "Could you please tell my son
她说"你能告诉我儿子

882
00:44:01,280 --> 00:44:04,580
to stop eating so much sugar?"
不要吃太多糖吗?"

883
00:44:04,580 --> 00:44:10,460
So Gandhi looks at the child intensely and says,
于是甘地注视着那个孩子说

884
00:44:10,590 --> 00:44:15,610
"Son, stop eating too much sugar."
"孩子 不要再吃太多糖"

885
00:44:18,630 --> 00:44:19,940
And that's it.
就是这样

886
00:44:21,520 --> 00:44:26,760
The woman is obviously perplexed and musters up her courage,
那个女人很困惑 她鼓起勇气

887
00:44:26,760 --> 00:44:29,560
and says, "Mahatma, thank you very much.
说"圣雄 非常感谢

888
00:44:29,560 --> 00:44:31,390
I'm sure he will stop eating too much sugar,
我肯定他不会再吃太多糖

889
00:44:31,390 --> 00:44:36,060
but why couldn't you tell him this a month ago,
但为什么不在一个月前告诉他

890
00:44:36,350 --> 00:44:38,970
when I came all the way here?"
在我长途赶来的时候?"

891
00:44:38,970 --> 00:44:42,920
And he said, "Well, madam, because a month ago,
他说"夫人 因为一个月前

892
00:44:42,920 --> 00:44:44,960
I was eating too much sugar."
我也吃太多糖"

893
00:44:51,090 --> 00:44:52,700
Yeah, I know, it's a very sophisticated joke--
