因为在很多方面 这听上去像神秘主义

1070
00:55:17,110 --> 00:55:19,650
And part of it is mystical-- still not understandable--
一部分是很神秘 仍无法理解

1071
00:55:19,650 --> 00:55:22,770
but we are going to talk about as much as we know--
但我们会谈到我们所知的

1072
00:55:22,770 --> 00:55:24,960
why it works and how it works.
信念为什么会起作用及如何起作用

1073
00:55:25,840 --> 00:55:29,350
There is unfortunately a lot of misunderstanding about optimism.
可惜 人们对乐观主义有很多误解

1074
00:55:29,900 --> 00:55:32,640
Because the self-help movement in many ways
因为自助运动在很多方面

1075
00:55:32,640 --> 00:55:37,930
is about telling us how it's all about the power of the mind,
是在告诉我们信念力量是怎么回事

1076
00:55:38,640 --> 00:55:41,060
talk about "Think and grow rich", the book;
提到《思考致富》那本书

1077
00:55:41,060 --> 00:55:42,930
we'll talk about the secrets
我们会讨论各种秘密

1078
00:55:43,190 --> 00:55:46,420
which is about creating our reality through our thoughts.
它们如何通过思想创造现实

1079
00:55:46,820 --> 00:55:49,980
And there's some truth to these-- but only some truth.
其中有些是事实 但仅是部分

1080
00:55:49,980 --> 00:55:53,930
We are going to bridge Ivory tower and Main Street,
我们将连通象牙塔和主街

1081
00:55:53,930 --> 00:55:58,600
and show the science and also the danger behind that belief.
说明那个信仰背后的科学和危险

1082
00:56:00,750 --> 00:56:02,940
Most importantly, how do we apply?
最重要的是如何应用?

1083
00:56:02,940 --> 00:56:05,180
How do we enhance the belief in ourselves
如何加强我们的信念

1084
00:56:05,180 --> 00:56:06,610
if there's such high correlation
如果真有这么紧密的关联

1085
00:56:06,610 --> 00:56:08,640
and there's a very high correlation
如果希望

1086
00:56:08,640 --> 00:56:10,860
and predictive power to a sense of hope,
乐观主义和信念真的

1087
00:56:10,860 --> 00:56:13,620
to a sense of optimism, to beliefs.
有着非常紧密的关联和预测力

1088
00:56:13,620 --> 00:56:16,170
If they so much determine our outcome,
如果它们决定我们的产出

1089
00:56:16,170 --> 00:56:18,010
in the athletic field,
无论在体育场上

1090
00:56:19,540 --> 00:56:22,100
in the workplace, in a relationship--
还是在工作地点 在人际关系上

1091
00:56:22,100 --> 00:56:25,200
if it matters so much, then how can we raise our beliefs?
如果它如此重要 那么该如何加强信念？

1092
00:56:25,200 --> 00:56:29,700
And we'll talk about work by Bandura on self-efficacy,
我们会谈到Bandura对自我效能的研究

1093
00:56:29,700 --> 00:56:32,460
or by Nathaniel Branden on self-esteem.
谈到Nathaniel Branden对自尊的研究

1094
00:56:35,400 --> 00:56:39,040
How we can make a dream into reality--
如何才能将梦想变成现实

1095
00:56:39,040 --> 00:56:40,910
whether it's political dream--
可以是政治梦想

1096
00:56:40,910 --> 00:56:44,340
we'll talk about Martin Luther King's dream approach-
我们将谈到马丁路德金的"梦想法"

1097
00:56:44,340 --> 00:56:46,470
how he did it and what he did;
他是如何做到 做了什么

1098
00:56:46,750 --> 00:56:48,570
or a personal dream,
也可以是个人梦想

1099
00:56:49,540 --> 00:56:54,050
where we'll talk about the work of Herbert Benson as well as Bandura.
我们会谈到Herbert Benson和Bandura

1100
00:56:55,630 --> 00:56:57,070
Once again, the Buddha,
再一次引用佛的话

1101
00:56:57,070 --> 00:56:58,080
"We are what we think.
"境随心转

1102
00:56:58,090 --> 00:57:00,330
All that we are arises with our thoughts.
全由意念升起

1103
00:57:00,330 --> 00:57:03,090
With our thoughts, we make our world."
我们的念头造就了世界"

1104
00:57:03,830 --> 00:57:07,450
Again, this was a claim made thousands of years ago.
这是几千年前的一个主张

1105
00:57:07,450 --> 00:57:08,280
What I want to do now
现在我要做的

1106
00:57:08,280 --> 00:57:12,770
is focus on the scientific foundation of this claim.
是专注于这个主张的科学基础

1107
00:57:13,910 --> 00:57:19,000
And I'll start by talking about Pygmalion in the classroom.
我会从皮格马利翁开始讲起

1108
00:57:20,150 --> 00:57:23,900
The source of the word, Pygmalion is ancient Greece.
"Pygmalion"是古希腊语

1109
00:57:25,610 --> 00:57:28,100
Pygmalion was a sculptor.
皮格马利翁是个雕刻家

1110
00:57:30,840 --> 00:57:36,570
And what he did was when he came of age looking for his ideal woman.
成年后他开始寻找理想中的女人

1111
00:57:36,570 --> 00:57:38,100
He wanted to get married.
他想结婚

1112
00:57:38,100 --> 00:57:41,330
So he went and looked around Athens where he lived;
他在雅典城里寻找

1113
00:57:41,330 --> 00:57:44,620
he looked around the all of Greece;
找遍整个希腊

1114
00:57:44,620 --> 00:57:46,780
he looked around the Greek Empire;
找遍整个希腊帝国

1115
00:57:46,780 --> 00:57:51,530
he looked beyond the Greek Empire, looking for his ideal woman--
去希腊帝国以外寻找 寻找他理想中的女人

1116
00:57:51,530 --> 00:57:54,020
a woman whom he could marry.
一个能和他结婚的女人

1117
00:57:54,650 --> 00:57:56,150
And he couldn't find her,
但没有找到

1118
00:57:56,150 --> 00:57:57,670
no matter where he looked.
不论去哪里找

1119
00:57:57,670 --> 00:57:58,720
I mean it's understandable--
这是可以理解的

1120
00:57:58,720 --> 00:58:04,000
this was before 1879 which was when Red Cliff was founded,
那是1879年之前 雷德克利夫学院还没成立

1121
00:58:06,160 --> 00:58:08,480
and long before Harvard became co-ed.
远在哈佛成为男女合校之前

1122
00:58:08,480 --> 00:58:13,780
So he couldn't find his ideal woman and he went back to Athens.
他找不到理想中的女人 于是他返回雅典

1123
00:58:15,080 --> 00:58:16,310
And he said to himself.
他对自己说

1124
00:58:16,310 --> 00:58:19,050
"Well, instead of finding that ideal woman,
"我不再寻找理想中的女人

1125
00:58:19,340 --> 00:58:21,960
I will create a sculpture"-- as he was a sculptor,
我要雕刻一座雕像"因为他是雕刻家

1126
00:58:21,960 --> 00:58:24,910
"I will create a sculpture in her image."
"我会以她的形象雕刻一座雕像"

1127
00:58:24,910 --> 00:58:26,560
And he created that sculpture.
他雕刻出那座雕像

1128
00:58:26,560 --> 00:58:28,250
And when he looked at her,
当他看着她时

1129
00:58:28,610 --> 00:58:33,550
he was so overwhelmed with emotion and sadness
他被激动之情和悲伤淹没

1130
00:58:33,550 --> 00:58:34,700
that he couldn't find her,
因为他找不到她

1131
00:58:34,700 --> 00:58:36,680
that he began to cry.
于是他开始哭泣

1132
00:58:37,630 --> 00:58:42,940
And then Zeus, Athena and especially Aphrodite,
宙斯 雅典娜 特别是阿芙罗狄蒂

1133
00:58:42,940 --> 00:58:51,500
looking down on him, took mercy and brought the statue to life.
俯视他 深感同情 于是把雕像变活

1134
00:58:51,710 --> 00:58:55,610
And of course, they lived happily ever after.
当然他们幸福地生活下去

1135
00:58:55,610 --> 00:58:58,470
So this is the source of the word, Pygmalion.
这是这个词的由来

1136
00:58:58,470 --> 00:59:02,930
Pygmalion was then taken by George Bernard Shaw,
然后萧伯纳借助这个词

1137
00:59:02,930 --> 00:59:06,030
who created a play based on a similar idea
创作了一部情节类似的戏剧

1138
00:59:06,030 --> 00:59:09,870
which was made into a musical, "My Fair Lady".
后来被改编成音乐剧《窈窕淑女》

1139
00:59:09,870 --> 00:59:13,460
The idea here is how Higgins,
说的是Higgins

1140
00:59:13,460 --> 00:59:15,460
doctor, linguist,
一位博士 语言学家

1141
00:59:15,460 --> 00:59:21,540
took a flower girl and molded her in the sense into being royalty.
如何把一个卖花女塑造成贵族

1142
00:59:21,540 --> 00:59:23,280
What of course happened through the story
当然故事讲完时

1143
00:59:23,280 --> 00:59:26,970
was that she molded him more and transformed him.
是她塑造了他 改变了他

1144
00:59:26,970 --> 00:59:29,790
Fascinating story and very important story at the time.
非常精彩的故事 当时很重要的故事

1145
00:59:29,790 --> 00:59:32,630
Because it challenged the whole class system,
因为它挑战了整个阶级体系

1146
00:59:32,630 --> 00:59:36,330
that people are born into a certain place and cannot--
人生来就有阶级 不能

1147
00:59:36,330 --> 00:59:38,460
and should not-- be moved.
也不应该被改变

1148
00:59:38,460 --> 00:59:41,790
So a very important play at that time, as well as today.
在当时是很重要的戏剧 今天也是如此

1149
00:59:42,730 --> 00:59:45,420
About Pygmalion and people can be changed,
皮格马利翁和人是可以被改变

1150
00:59:45,420 --> 00:59:47,220
can be transformed.
被改造的

1151
00:59:49,040 --> 00:59:51,080
In the 1960s,
1960年代

1152
00:59:52,740 --> 00:59:55,630
Robert Rosenthal who was the head of our department for many years--
Robert Rosenthal曾在本系担任多年主任

1153
00:59:55,630 --> 00:59:57,850
he's now in UC Riverside--
现在就职加州大学河滨分校

1154
00:59:57,850 --> 01:00:01,550
took this idea of Pygmalion and applied it in the classroom.
把皮格马利翁的思想应用于课堂

1155
01:00:02,100 --> 01:00:05,580
Here is what he did. Rosenthal went into a group of random schools.
他是这么做的 Rosenthal随便走进几间学校

1156
01:00:05,820 --> 01:00:08,410
And what he did there was went to the students,
去到学生中间

1157
01:00:08,410 --> 01:00:10,200
had them take a test
让他们接受一次测验

1158
01:00:10,200 --> 01:00:13,170
and then go to their teachers after and tell the teachers,
然后去找他们的老师并告诉他们

1159
01:00:13,170 --> 01:00:16,500
"Your students just took a new test that was devised--
"你们的学生刚接受了一个新测试

1160
01:00:16,500 --> 01:00:21,690
a new academic test which is called "the fast spurters' test".
一种新的学业测试 叫作快速迸发者测试"

1161
01:00:21,690 --> 01:00:25,120
What that means is that we identify students
测试能让我们找出

1162
01:00:25,120 --> 01:00:27,220
who are going to take a big leap,
将在新学年在学业上

1163
01:00:27,220 --> 01:00:30,020
intellectual leap forward in this coming year,
取得巨大进步的学生

1164
01:00:30,020 --> 01:00:32,200
a spurt forward in this coming year.
在新学年取得巨大进步

1165
01:00:32,200 --> 01:00:33,760
In other words, what he was saying--
换言之 他的意思是

1166
01:00:33,760 --> 01:00:37,060
it identifies students with highest potential.
测试找出最有潜力的学生

1167
01:00:39,050 --> 01:00:43,890
And what he found then was when he told these students--
他发现…

1168
01:00:43,890 --> 01:00:46,680
the teachers-- what he told these teachers was that
他对这些老师说的是

1169
01:00:46,840 --> 01:00:49,390
"it is just not a FYI-- you cannot tell the students this.
"这只是仅供参考 不能向学生透露

1170
01:00:49,390 --> 01:00:51,450
We don't want any discrimination in your school,
我们不希望学校有歧视行为

1171
01:00:51,450 --> 01:00:54,460
but just so you know, these are your fast spurters.
只是让你们知道 这些学生有巨大潜力

1172
01:00:54,460 --> 01:00:56,560
It's a new test, newly devised.
这是一项新发明的测试

1173
01:00:58,480 --> 01:01:00,800
Just so you know." Unbeknownst to the teachers,
只有你们知道就好"老师们不知道的是

1174
01:01:00,800 --> 01:01:03,330
the actual test which was given to those students
对学生进行的测试

1175
01:01:03,330 --> 01:01:06,760
was a regular off-the-shelf IQ test.
只是普通的现成的智商测试

1176
01:01:07,560 --> 01:01:12,680
Also unbeknownst to the teachers was these students names,
老师们也不知道这些所谓的

1177
01:01:13,280 --> 01:01:16,910
who were deemed "the fast spurters"/"high potential students",
"快速迸发者"或者潜力巨大的学生

1178
01:01:17,950 --> 01:01:21,690
were literally randomly picked out from a hat.
都是从一个帽子抓阄抓出来的

1179
01:01:22,740 --> 01:01:24,860
So there were regular students,
他们都是普通学生

1180
01:01:25,150 --> 01:01:26,860
like all other students,
和别的学生没有区别

1181
01:01:27,840 --> 01:01:30,810
but the teachers thought they were "fast spurters".
但老师们以为他们有巨大潜力

1182
01:01:31,180 --> 01:01:32,870
Robert Rosenthal leaves the school,
Robert Rosenthal离开学校

1183
01:01:32,870 --> 01:01:34,970
comes back in the end of the year.
学年结束时再回来

1184
01:01:35,460 --> 01:01:38,790
And here's what he finds-- he looks at their English scores:
他发现 他查看他们的英语成绩

1185
01:01:38,790 --> 01:01:41,530
the "fast spurters" improved significantly
"快速迸发"学生有明显进步

1186
01:01:41,530 --> 01:01:45,600
more than any of the other students.
比任何学生的进步都快

1187
01:01:46,270 --> 01:01:47,790
He looked at their maths scores,
他查看他们的数学成绩

1188
01:01:47,790 --> 01:01:49,510
because English is not really objective
因为英语不够客观

1189
01:01:49,510 --> 01:01:51,270
and you know maybe it was the teachers
也许是老师们

1190
01:01:51,270 --> 01:01:52,850
who thought they were better than they were really.
觉得某些学生英语更好

1191
01:01:52,850 --> 01:01:55,340
So he looked at their maths, their objective scores.
于是他查看他们的数学 客观的成绩

1192
01:01:56,820 --> 01:01:59,380
These students improved significantly
这些学生也有明显进步

1193
01:01:59,380 --> 01:02:01,750
more than any of the other students.
比其他任何学生的进步都大

1194
01:02:03,570 --> 01:02:05,160
But here is the clincher:
接下来才是有决定性的结果

1195
01:02:05,160 --> 01:02:08,960
Robert Rosenthal administered once again an IQ test
Robert Rosenthal又对所有学生

1196
01:02:08,960 --> 01:02:10,600
for all the students.
进行了一次智商测试

1197
01:02:11,690 --> 01:02:15,370
And what he found was the students who were labeled--
他发现被标签为

1198
01:02:16,290 --> 01:02:18,030
randomly so, but who were labeled--
被随机地标签为"快速迸发"的学生

1199
01:02:18,030 --> 01:02:25,310
"fast spurters", their IQ increased significantly over the year
智商在一年间有很大增加

1200
01:02:25,540 --> 01:02:29,530
and maintained that increase in a longitudinal study.
而且在长期研究中保持着增加

1201
01:02:30,020 --> 01:02:31,760
Now this is my bog I mean:
这让人不解

1202
01:02:31,760 --> 01:02:34,180
IQ is supposed to be in your intelligent quotient
智商

1203
01:02:34,180 --> 01:02:35,940
that you are born with!
本来是生而有之的

1204
01:02:35,940 --> 01:02:36,790
It's immutable.
它是恒定的

1205
01:02:36,790 --> 01:02:39,620
It doesn't change from the day you were born to the day you die--
从出生到死亡时都不会改变

1206
01:02:39,620 --> 01:02:41,680
or so they thought.
或者说他们这样认为

1207
01:02:43,140 --> 01:02:46,770
It changed significantly just based the belief
但它却因为

1208
01:02:46,770 --> 01:02:51,620
that the teacher had in her/his students.
老师对学生的信念而改变

1209
01:02:52,120 --> 01:02:55,750
Belief as self-fulfilling prophecies.
信念即自我实现预言

1210
01:02:58,490 --> 01:03:00,310
What happened in the study?
这项研究说明了什么？

1211
01:03:00,310 --> 01:03:02,810
Was it that the teachers were fooled?
老师们被骗了吗？

1212
01:03:03,330 --> 01:03:09,190
And suddenly were made to see an illusion? No.
突然产生幻象? 不是的

1213
01:03:09,190 --> 01:03:11,500
It was that they were alluded before.
是因为他们之前被欺骗

1214
01:03:13,270 --> 01:03:14,850
and the illusion was that they didn't see
幻象是他们看不到

1215
01:03:14,850 --> 01:03:17,820
what is right in front of their very eyes,
就在他们眼前的东西

1216
01:03:17,820 --> 01:03:23,040
which is the potential inherent in every single student.
即每个学生都有潜力

1217
01:03:24,010 --> 01:03:27,420
And then Robert Rosenthal comes and fools them in a sense,
Robert Rosenthal来到 可以说是骗了他们

1218
01:03:27,420 --> 01:03:30,410
but "fools" them into seeing what has been there all along.
"骗"他们注意到一直在眼前的东西

1219
01:03:31,910 --> 01:03:35,150
Before Rosenthal, they didn't see children on the bus.
在那之前 他们没注意到车上的孩子

1220
01:03:35,950 --> 01:03:36,860
So to speak.
可以这么说

1221
01:03:36,860 --> 01:03:40,030
After that, they suddenly in some children
之后 突然他们在一些孩子身上

1222
01:03:40,030 --> 01:03:42,710
saw the potential that was there all along.
看到一直都有的潜力

1223
01:03:45,280 --> 01:03:48,710
And they appreciated that potential and that potential appreciated.
他们欣赏那种潜力 潜力得到升值

1224
01:03:48,710 --> 01:03:51,440
They watered, they shed a light to it
他们灌溉 播撒阳光

1225
01:03:51,440 --> 01:03:54,590
and the seed germinated and grew.
种子开始发芽生长

1226
01:03:54,930 --> 01:03:58,730
This is exactly what Marva Collins does day in and day out in school.
这正是Marva Collins每天在学校里做的事

1227
01:03:58,730 --> 01:04:00,440
She seed the potential that is there;
她看到存在的潜力

1228
01:04:00,440 --> 01:04:01,620
she's not even inventing something.
她不是发明家

1229
01:04:01,620 --> 01:04:04,120
She's not detached from reality.
没有脱离现实

1230
01:04:04,120 --> 01:04:07,910
It's rather the people who don't see the potential in other people
是人们看不到他人身上的潜力

1231
01:04:08,440 --> 01:04:11,360
as well as in themselves as we'll discuss.
也看不到自己身上的潜力 我们会讨论到

1232
01:04:11,360 --> 01:04:13,940
They are not seeing the full reality.
他们没有看到整个现实

1233
01:04:13,940 --> 01:04:15,550
They are only seeing part of it.
只看到一部分

1234
01:04:15,550 --> 01:04:18,330
They are completely missing the children on the bus.
完全无视车上的孩子们

1235
01:04:18,520 --> 01:04:22,920
And we know how easy it is to miss part of reality,
我们知道无视一部分现实是多么容易

1236
01:04:22,920 --> 01:04:25,670
even they are right in front of our very eyes.
就算他们就在我们眼前

1237
01:04:26,960 --> 01:04:28,990
Or it often takes a question--
经常需要被问及

