as a result of just changing the situation.
仅仅是在改变情境的情况下

1439
01:15:25,830 --> 01:15:29,010
Same distance, same chart, same everything.
相同的距离 相同的表 什么都一样

1440
01:15:29,010 --> 01:15:30,680
Different situation.
只是情境不同

1441
01:15:34,080 --> 01:15:39,130
The question is how do we create a positive situation.
问题是我们如何创造积极情境

1442
01:15:40,910 --> 01:15:46,330
How can we create a situation that improves us with the role.
如何创造一个利用角色自我改进的情境

1443
01:15:46,330 --> 01:15:49,340
And I want to share with you couple of studies--
我想介绍两个研究

1444
01:15:49,340 --> 01:15:53,920
I'll share one study and then another later-- about the environment.
先说第一个再说第二个 关于环境

1445
01:15:53,920 --> 01:15:55,550
First of all, the work of Barge,
首先是Barge的研究

1446
01:15:55,550 --> 01:15:58,410
priming is when we have subconscious or conscious priming.
影射分为潜意识和有意识影射

1447
01:15:58,410 --> 01:16:02,750
For example, you are looking at a screen
比如你看着一个屏幕

1448
01:16:02,750 --> 01:16:07,490
and for just a few milliseconds, a word appears.
在几毫秒内闪过一个词

1449
01:16:07,490 --> 01:16:08,880
And the word primes you.
这个词让你有了准备

1450
01:16:08,880 --> 01:16:10,090
There is a lot of research on
有很多关于如何利用

1451
01:16:10,090 --> 01:16:13,860
how we can prime your negatively with stereotypes for example,
典型消极情况进行影射的研究 比如

1452
01:16:13,860 --> 01:16:15,220
with prejudices.
使用偏见

1453
01:16:15,220 --> 01:16:18,020
Or positively-- but not enough from positively.
或者积极的 但对积极影射的研究不够

1454
01:16:18,020 --> 01:16:19,640
So here's a story done by Barge.
Barge做了下面的实验

1455
01:16:19,640 --> 01:16:25,110
He primed people with words associated with old.
他用与"老"有关的词影射人

1456
01:16:25,430 --> 01:16:28,560
So for example, word such as old,
比如"老"这个词

1457
01:16:28,560 --> 01:16:36,120
word such as stick,
"拐杖"

1458
01:16:36,560 --> 01:16:43,500
word such as Florida--
"佛罗里达"

1459
01:16:45,250 --> 01:16:47,930
that's one of the words he primed people with.
他用这个词影射人们

1460
01:16:48,290 --> 01:16:50,780
So he primed people with "old" words.
他用与老有关的词影射人们

1461
01:16:50,780 --> 01:16:53,580
And then he had them take a comparative and control group
然后他对比他们和对照组的

1462
01:16:53,580 --> 01:16:56,590
an intelligence test and a memory test.
智力和记忆力测试结果

1463
01:16:56,590 --> 01:17:01,120
The memory of the people who were primed with "old" words.
用与"老"相关的词影射过的人的记忆力

1464
01:17:02,100 --> 01:17:05,070
They performed the worst than the control group.
他们的表现比对照组差

1465
01:17:07,840 --> 01:17:13,840
Second, he looked at these people
第二 他观察这些人

1466
01:17:13,840 --> 01:17:18,250
and measured how fast they walk from
记录他们从实验地点

1467
01:17:18,690 --> 01:17:21,840
where their experiment was to the elevator.
走到电梯的时间

1468
01:17:22,280 --> 01:17:24,890
And also had blind evaluators--
还找来盲测员

1469
01:17:24,890 --> 01:17:26,840
people who didn't know which condition they were in,
那些不了解情况的人

1470
01:17:27,930 --> 01:17:30,120
evaluate how they were walking.
评估他们的走路

1471
01:17:30,120 --> 01:17:33,910
So the people who were primed with old actually walked
用"老"影射过的人行走起来

1472
01:17:33,910 --> 01:17:37,440
more stoop than the other people.
真得比其他人更弯腰驼背

1473
01:17:37,440 --> 01:17:41,150
And they walk significantly slower toward the elevator,
走向电梯的速度明显慢

1474
01:17:41,730 --> 01:17:44,790
not knowing that they were primed with old words.
虽然不知道自己被与"老"相关的字影射过

1475
01:17:46,060 --> 01:17:48,320
They walk slower toward the elevator.,
但他们走向电梯的速度

1476
01:17:48,680 --> 01:17:53,680
then the people who were not primed with these old words,
比没有受到影响的人慢

1477
01:17:55,790 --> 01:17:58,080
subconscious completely.
完全是潜意识的

1478
01:17:58,080 --> 01:18:00,470
And then they did something priming people with words
然后他们用与"成就"相关的词

1479
01:18:00,470 --> 01:18:02,130
related to an achievement.
影射人们

1480
01:18:02,130 --> 01:18:03,310
The people who were primed,
受到影射的人

1481
01:18:03,310 --> 01:18:07,510
subconsciously with words related to achievement,
用与"成就"有关的词进行潜意识影射的人

1482
01:18:09,170 --> 01:18:11,390
did better on tests than control group.
测试结果比对照组好

1483
01:18:11,390 --> 01:18:12,950
Their memory improved,
他们的记忆力得到改进

1484
01:18:12,950 --> 01:18:16,560
and they persisted more on difficult tasks.
面对困难任务时更有持久力

1485
01:18:16,560 --> 01:18:19,950
And the question is-- the thing we'll talk about next time--
问题是…下次课我会谈到的是

1486
